reviewText: Happily Ever After is an unofficial sequel to the Disney film ''Snow White And The Seven Dwarfs''. In the film, Snow White meets with the dwarfs magical cousins called The Seven Dwarfelles, and they must travel to the realm of doom to save the Prince from the evil Lord Maliss.This movie has great voice acting and a really lovely and emotional ending that made me cry. I totally recommend this movie to anyone.
Title: N/A

reviewText: Come on, it's a good movie.  Sure, Lord Malice is cookie-cuter to the extreme, but it's an animated children's fairy tale, what do you expect?  I actually always thought that Malice was the most frightening of all of the Disney villians (even though this isn't Disney).  I was dissapointed that the original seven dwarves were nowhere to be seen, but their female cousins are cute and likable enough, espescially Thunderella and Critterena.  And I know everybody hates the music, but I actually thought it was pretty good, despite the cliched lyrics in some of the songs.  And the Ed Anser-voiced owl Scowl was pretty funny.  Overall this is a great movie and your kids will love it.  Very underrated.

reviewText: This is NOT a sequel to the Disney film of Snow White. Rather, one could see this as a sequel to the original Snow White story, as this is set after the conclusion of the story. I really liked the character design of Snow White - better than the Disney character design, I must admit (especially Snow White's dress) The seven Dwarfelles are cute, and Lord Maliss could be considered a cookie-cutter villain (he was the evil Queen's brother, making him Snow White's step-uncle) but I actually liked this movie.

reviewText: The animation is lousy, music was below second rate, characters were poorly designed and written, the voices awful and some annoying, the story line...well, dumb does not even beging to explain it, and beyond boring. The kids even couldnt finish it.Not trying to be mean...really I am not.  I always try to give everything a fair try but this is sooooo bad. I found this at a yard sale for a $1 and it was a waste of even that. Sorry. They thought they could capitalize on the orginal and feel so short it is not even funny.  Honestly deserves a negative star.
summary: Stupid, stupid, stupid ...and that is being nice

reviewText: It is better to think of this as a sequal to the Grimms tale, not the Disney film. The Dwarfs are not in here only because Disney said no. But that's okay. Muddy, Sunburn, Critterina, Marina, Blossom, Noonbeam and  Thunderella are just as good. Lord MALISS could very well be the brother of  the unamed Wicked Queen. The soundtrack is one of the best that goes with  film. I saw this when it first came out in 1993. I was seven or eight years  old then. I really loved this film then and now. But I appreciate it more  these days. The only slight quibble is that I saw a more pleasant Mother  Nature in "The Year Without a Santa Clause".
summary: Picks right up where the original story left off.
